The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 PCB appoints Waqar till World Cup

Karachi: Former captain Waqar Younis was on Wednesday appointed Pakistan bowling coach until next years World Cup in the West Indies while another former captain Zaheer Abbas was named team manager for the tour of Sri Lanka. 

The decisions were made on Wednesday after lengthy discussions between skipper Inzamam-ul Haq, coach Bob Woolmer and PCB chairman Shaharyar Khan in Lahore where the reconditioning camp for this months Sri Lanka tour started. 

It is definitely a great honour and I just cant wait to get back to the nets, an elated Waqar said, but refused to discuss the terms and conditions of his contract. 

Waqar took 373 Test and 416 one-day wickets during his illustrious career. 

Waqar said Inzamam remained the captain of the ship and together with Woolmer, he was keen to form a winning team management. 

